1
00:00:29,840 --> 00:00:32,200
And they want us to sign
with the studio.

2
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:35,000
You're gonna become an actor
without even asking me?

3
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,160
Can't open the files.

4
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:37,240
How's it going, sir?

5
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:40,080
Can I have a little more time
to fix it up?

6
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:43,120
Okay.

7
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:49,560
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

8
00:01:15,750 --> 00:01:16,750
Ugh.

9
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:22,520
I'm sorry. We're late because of me.

10
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:24,600
Hey, don't apologize.

11
00:01:25,010 --> 00:01:26,620
I don't really wanna be an actor.

12
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,880
I'm here just to support you.

13
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:34,480
Cut it out. Don't spiral.

14
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:37,400
Tell you what?
I'll try calling Phi Cha.

15
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:41,840
Don't bother.
I doubt she'll pick up.

16
00:01:43,510 --> 00:01:44,510
Let's just head back.

17
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:56,080
Hey, wait.
What are you two doing here?

18
00:01:56,440 --> 00:02:00,080
Well,...nobody was there
in the casting room.

19
00:02:00,230 --> 00:02:04,080
What? We're in the other room,
right there.

20
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:07,320
Come on, follow me. Quick, quick.

21
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:24,040
I'm sorry we were late.

22
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:26,840
Something...
completely out of our hands came up.

23
00:02:27,030 --> 00:02:29,600
Going forward,
please try to be on time.

24
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:32,490
Of course. It won't happen again.

25
00:02:33,260 --> 00:02:36,580
So...what have you prepared
for us today?

26
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,200
A scene from my grandpa's novel.

27
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:39,480
Between Us in the Deep Forest?

28
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:42,200
- Yes.
- Seriously?

29
00:02:42,420 --> 00:02:44,960
Uh...what's it even about?

30
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:49,000
Oh, come on.
How do you not know it?

31
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,400
It's a BL novel
his grandfather wrote. Really good.

32
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:57,100
Uh...I'll give you a moment.

33
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:59,870
- We'll start in five.
- Thanks.

34
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,640
Hey, take a breath.

35
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:20,600
Huh.

36
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:24,150
I don't know.
I suddenly feel so nervous.

37
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,440
Well.

38
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:28,900
It happens

39
00:03:29,490 --> 00:03:31,520
when something
really matters to you.

40
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,240
I get it too
before big soccer matches.

41
00:03:35,010 --> 00:03:38,300
My coach just says we train hard
to enjoy the game.

42
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,240
Hmph.

43
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,400
Grandpa trained us well too.

44
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:47,200
So let's just enjoy the scene.

45
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,800
Mm-hmm.

46
00:03:59,310 --> 00:04:00,920
Why did you pick this scene?

47
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:05,400
Hmm...when I read it,
I felt the weight.

48
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:09,280
I thought it would pull me in,
and the audience too.

49
00:04:12,860 --> 00:04:14,040
But it's tough.

50
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:18,000
Grandpa,
always trying to kill our vibe.

51
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:22,080
These roles don't feel like you
right now. Will it land?

52
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:25,200
I'm worried the judges
will send you packing.

53
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:28,480
I don't think
it's that far off from us.

54
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:31,120
And we're about
Anan and Somporn's age.

55
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:33,000
For something this hard,

56
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:35,500
we should score big
if we pull it off.

57
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:39,920
Fair enough.
Any questions before you go in?

58
00:04:40,340 --> 00:04:44,430
Hmm...how about Somporn's life?

59
00:04:45,080 --> 00:04:46,760
How broken is he, really?

60
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:51,240
Feelings ain't exactly fan speed
you can just dial up or down.

61
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:52,700
He is real sad.

62
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:56,760
He'll never see Anan again.

63
00:04:58,180 --> 00:04:59,620
And if by chance he does,

64
00:05:00,380 --> 00:05:02,060
it won't be the same between them.

65
00:05:02,640 --> 00:05:05,480
But if...
they loved each other that much,

66
00:05:06,050 --> 00:05:08,090
shouldn't Anan
try to hold Somporn back?

67
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,600
Back then,

68
00:05:10,370 --> 00:05:13,780
a love like that was frowned upon

69
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,570
making a life together impossible.

70
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,380
Even the two of them

71
00:05:20,110 --> 00:05:22,680
didn't fully understand
what they were feeling.

72
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,840
And Anan's love for Somporn

73
00:05:26,020 --> 00:05:29,200
was deep enough that he was willing

74
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:32,720
to let Somporn go.

75
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,800
Wow, Anan really is something else.

76
00:05:36,830 --> 00:05:39,930
Yeah. He was that resolute.

77
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,800
And did Somporn truly love Anan?

78
00:05:43,290 --> 00:05:44,360
Hey, Save.

79
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:47,700
Have you actually read my novel?

80
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:52,200
I did. I'm just
not sure about this part.

81
00:05:52,230 --> 00:05:55,230
I feel he's torn. Hard to read.

82
00:05:56,910 --> 00:05:59,840
Not all that goes unwritten

83
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,980
between the lines

84
00:06:06,050 --> 00:06:07,160
is lost.

85
00:06:08,030 --> 00:06:12,160
Go back and carefully read it again.

86
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:16,560
Try to fathom
what Somporn is feeling.

87
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:41,600
It's been a long time.

88
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:44,430
How have you been?

89
00:06:46,130 --> 00:06:48,640
Nothing much. You?

90
00:06:49,860 --> 00:06:51,080
Nothing new, really.

91
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:59,140
I dream about the forest a lot.

92
00:06:59,810 --> 00:07:01,040
Do you ever?

93
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:03,420
Sometimes.

94
00:07:05,930 --> 00:07:08,320
A fun adventure turned daunting;

95
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:11,480
we nearly didn't make it out alive.

96
00:07:13,950 --> 00:07:15,040
Luck played her part

97
00:07:16,690 --> 00:07:18,040
and saved our lives

98
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,680
from the tiger's claws.

99
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:22,700
Mm-hmm.

100
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,520
It almost had us though.

101
00:07:27,650 --> 00:07:31,030
Come to think of it.
It was fun because of you.

102
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:36,020
Had I gone solo or with anyone else,
it wouldn't have been fun,

103
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:38,640
lonely even.

104
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,430
We should return
to the forest again.

105
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,400
What say you?

106
00:07:54,230 --> 00:07:55,230
Yeah.

107
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:59,880
Next month,
the rainy season will end.

108
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,560
Get yourself ready.

109
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,280
I'll let you know the date.

110
00:08:04,520 --> 00:08:05,520
You know,

111
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:08,240
I want to go.

112
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,800
But I won't be able to.

113
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:17,840
Oh? Why not?

114
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:54,420
"Wedding Invitation: Anong
and Somporn, December 15, 2026."

115
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:00,440
You're getting married?

116
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,840
Mm-hmm.

117
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:17,560
Who is Anong?

118
00:09:21,810 --> 00:09:23,360
Daughter of Mom's friend.

119
00:09:24,920 --> 00:09:27,560
Oh, the one you mentioned before.

120
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,600
Mm-hmm.

121
00:09:33,810 --> 00:09:35,850
Big news.
Should've told me sooner.

122
00:09:36,310 --> 00:09:38,970
So I could get a sharp suit
tailored for your wedding.

123
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:41,360
I'm sorry.

124
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,690
Still working through it.

125
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:47,760
Yeah.

126
00:09:48,700 --> 00:09:51,640
Congratulations. Best of wishes.

127
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:54,040
Thank you.

128
00:09:55,790 --> 00:09:59,150
Come to the wedding if you could.

129
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,880
Absolutely.

130
00:10:02,570 --> 00:10:06,410
I wouldn't miss it for the world.

131
00:10:07,050 --> 00:10:10,970
It's your big day.
How could I miss it?

132
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:25,200
Will you...still go to the forest?

133
00:10:26,330 --> 00:10:29,880
Of course. The forest is my life.

134
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:31,800
Mm-hmm.

135
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:35,560
Live it well.

136
00:10:37,060 --> 00:10:38,080
Leave some for me too.

137
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,960
Yeah.

138
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,560
Don't worry.

139
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:46,360
You'll be on your own.

140
00:10:48,170 --> 00:10:49,440
Just watch your back.

141
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:55,280
In a tiger's claws,
no one comes to your aid.

142
00:10:57,890 --> 00:11:00,480
Then I shall eat that tiger.

143
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:06,560
I have to go now.

144
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:10,480
Time to pick up Anong.

145
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:13,520
Yeah, go.

146
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:17,040
I'm off.

147
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:19,720
See you at the wedding.

148
00:11:22,710 --> 00:11:23,730
Huh.

149
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,240
Drive safely.

150
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:32,280
Groom-to-be.

151
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:38,440
Mm-hmm.

152
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:14,960
Huh.

153
00:12:28,810 --> 00:12:30,520
Huh.

154
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:36,960
Phi Cha,
when will we hear the results?

155
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:40,100
Uh...not sure yet.

156
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:42,280
We'll need to talk it over
a bit more.

157
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,920
There're dozens of people
auditioning today.

158
00:12:46,570 --> 00:12:49,110
Hey, once we have the results,
I'll call you right away.

159
00:12:49,510 --> 00:12:50,510
Yeah?

160
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:55,360
Okay, thank you.

161
00:12:55,660 --> 00:12:58,040
- Thank you.
- Sure, sure. Get home safe.

162
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:31,480
You think...we made it?

163
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:33,360
Yeah.

164
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,640
Really?

165
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,600
Maybe.

166
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:39,520
But it's out of our hands now.

167
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:41,760
Did you give it everything?

168
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,200
Mm-hmm.

169
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:48,520
Then don't overthink it.
Wait for the call.

170
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,800
Yeah.

171
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,720
I just said don't overthink it.

172
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,080
I didn't.

173
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,280
Then why the face?

174
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,600
Let me drop you at your condo.

175
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:39,750
Go.

176
00:14:57,510 --> 00:14:59,640
How did it go
with the publisher, Grandpa?

177
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:02,640
They're proofreading it now.

178
00:15:03,190 --> 00:15:05,550
What about you?
Did you make it to the audition?

179
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,500
Just in time.

180
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,000
What did they say?

181
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,280
Hmm...

182
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,120
Let me ask you this.

183
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:18,600
I don't know what came over me.
I burst into tears mid-scene.

184
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:20,760
Nothing during rehearsal.

185
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:22,080
Really?

186
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,280
What happened to me?

187
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:27,000
I don't know either,

188
00:15:28,530 --> 00:15:30,400
but while writing, I cried too.

189
00:15:33,380 --> 00:15:35,000
Nop. There you go.

190
00:15:39,260 --> 00:15:41,120
"Wedding Invitation:
Kanda and Somsak"

191
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,600
Congratulations, Sak.

192
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:46,160
Thanks a lot.

193
00:15:46,190 --> 00:15:48,200
You and Kanda are perfect
for each other.

194
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:50,160
Hurry and find yours.

195
00:15:50,370 --> 00:15:52,440
Mine still hasn't come along.

196
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,400
Hope you'll find yours soon.

197
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:02,920
I think in this life,
I'm meant to stay single.

198
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:06,160
Probably no kids either.
I'll just help raise yours.

199
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:08,640
Not sure I can come to your wedding.

200
00:16:10,090 --> 00:16:12,570
Consider this...an early gift.

201
00:16:25,790 --> 00:16:26,960
Hold onto it for me.

202
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:29,820
A memory, okay?

203
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:32,920
I'll keep it safe.

204
00:16:33,880 --> 00:16:34,880
I have to run.

205
00:16:35,970 --> 00:16:36,970
Mm-hmm.

206
00:16:49,530 --> 00:16:50,530
Nop...

207
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:14,880
So when you were writing
the parting scene, you teared up.

208
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,400
Mm-hmm.

209
00:17:18,050 --> 00:17:22,440
Hmm? Is this clean?
I can barely make it out.

210
00:17:24,950 --> 00:17:25,950
Let me.

211
00:17:29,110 --> 00:17:32,910
It's as clean as it'll get.
Just throw it away.

212
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:39,690
So...do you understand Somporn now?

213
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:42,300
I do...

214
00:17:42,850 --> 00:17:43,870
maybe.

215
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:50,760
Put it back in the cabinet
where it was, would you?

216
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:11,950
Please...
just bear cucumbers already.

217
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:15,280
Been tending to these for months.
I'm so hopeless.

218
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:17,840
Once we get the cucumbers,

219
00:18:17,870 --> 00:18:21,040
I'll make stuffed cucumber soup
for everyone.

220
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,360
Should be right around
the school break.

221
00:18:23,590 --> 00:18:24,820
Let's see one cucumber first.

222
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:27,560
Hey, guys.

223
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:30,400
This school break, let's ask Grandpa
to take us on a trip?

224
00:18:30,660 --> 00:18:32,170
Yeah? Can we?

225
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:36,120
Of course. If his novel sells,
he'll take us out for sure.

226
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:38,080
Where do you want to go?

227
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:41,360
Hmm...the beach. I've never been.

228
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:43,560
Got it. I'll ask him.

229
00:18:43,560 --> 00:18:44,560
Thank you.

230
00:18:47,310 --> 00:18:49,680
Jingjai, come with me for a sec.

231
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:51,760
What's going on?

232
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:53,500
Come on, quick, quick.

233
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:54,500
Okay.

234
00:18:57,340 --> 00:18:58,400
Where's she going?

235
00:18:59,430 --> 00:19:00,430
Hey...

236
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:03,440
Ow.

237
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:04,560
Hmm?

238
00:19:06,230 --> 00:19:07,240
Is something off?

239
00:19:18,310 --> 00:19:19,320
Hello.

240
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:24,160
Mom, can I stay?
Let me stay with my friends.

241
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:28,480
Jingjai, don't be difficult.
I came all this way.

242
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:30,640
You have friends
back in Lampang too.

243
00:19:30,640 --> 00:19:32,800
But I want to stay
with my friends here.

244
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:35,520
You're the one who brought me here.

245
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,520
Now you're dragging me
somewhere else?

246
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:42,360
Snow said Grandpa's taking us
to the beach.

247
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:47,440
You've never taken me once.
I want to go with my friends.

248
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:50,130
Huk. Huk.

249
00:19:50,130 --> 00:19:52,240
I don't want to leave.

250
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:56,320
Hngh.

251
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,320
Jingjai.

252
00:19:57,460 --> 00:20:00,460
No. I'm not going. I'm not.

253
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:01,680
I'm not going.

254
00:20:01,710 --> 00:20:03,280
Jingjai, don't be difficult.

255
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:04,560
I'm not going.

256
00:20:05,140 --> 00:20:06,280
I'm not going.

257
00:20:07,950 --> 00:20:09,480
Thank you all so much.

258
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:11,960
I'm not going.

259
00:20:11,990 --> 00:20:13,310
Hngh...

260
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:15,120
Please, Auntie.

261
00:20:17,330 --> 00:20:19,600
- Don't take her away.
- That's right.

262
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:21,400
She is our friend.

263
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:23,840
Please don't take her.

264
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:26,000
We'll look after her well.

265
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:29,520
We promise she'll be happy here.

266
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:32,240
You can leave her with us.

267
00:20:32,450 --> 00:20:35,840
Whenever you miss her,
just come visit.

268
00:20:36,350 --> 00:20:39,030
- Please, we're begging you.
- Please, don't take her.

269
00:20:39,060 --> 00:20:41,170
- Can we ask you this?
- Please...

270
00:20:42,570 --> 00:20:44,800
Excuse us a moment.

271
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:46,840
Kids.

272
00:20:48,390 --> 00:20:51,120
Jingjai is going home
with her mother today.

273
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:56,360
I'll give you ten minutes.
Say your goodbyes.

274
00:21:10,290 --> 00:21:11,760
Thank you all so much.

275
00:21:26,530 --> 00:21:30,080
Come back whenever you miss us.

276
00:21:32,010 --> 00:21:34,290
Reach out anytime.

277
00:21:38,370 --> 00:21:41,320
The others gave you some snacks.
For the train ride.

278
00:21:54,170 --> 00:21:55,180
Take care.

279
00:22:00,420 --> 00:22:01,460
Don't cry now.

280
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:04,560
Jingjai. Let's go.

281
00:22:07,450 --> 00:22:08,450
Yes.

282
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:13,200
- Jingjai.
- Jingjai.

283
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:15,490
- Jingjai.
- Jingjai.

284
00:22:15,790 --> 00:22:16,800
Jingjai.

285
00:22:26,570 --> 00:22:29,640
- Have a safe trip.
- Safe trip.

286
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:33,920
- Good luck, Jingjai.
- Good luck, Jingjai.

287
00:22:34,060 --> 00:22:36,200
- Bye.
- Bye.

288
00:22:36,910 --> 00:22:39,040
Thank you all, kids. Well then...

289
00:22:41,070 --> 00:22:42,070
Bye.

290
00:22:47,750 --> 00:22:48,750
Bye.

291
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:52,200
We'll always think of you, Jingjai.

292
00:22:59,370 --> 00:23:00,800
That's just how life goes.

293
00:23:01,810 --> 00:23:04,240
All meetings end in partings.

294
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:07,110
But if you're meant
to find each other,

295
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:09,640
you'll meet again.

296
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:11,840
- Ho. Ho.
- Yeah.

297
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:21,270
- Has the studio contacted you?
- Not yet.

298
00:23:21,650 --> 00:23:22,650
Hmm.

299
00:23:28,260 --> 00:23:29,440
Is anyone home?

300
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:31,930
No one. Dad's out delivering.

301
00:23:32,260 --> 00:23:34,070
Mom, Grandpa, and Snow
are with the kids.

302
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:35,390
Hey.

303
00:23:35,630 --> 00:23:38,680
Plotting something?
Us, alone in an empty house?

304
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,000
What do you think?

305
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:02,240
You locked it?

306
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:04,880
So no one will interrupt.

307
00:24:08,270 --> 00:24:09,520
Whew.

308
00:24:13,990 --> 00:24:14,990
Come here.

309
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:17,280
Now?

310
00:24:17,310 --> 00:24:18,520
What's the matter?

311
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:20,360
Chickening out?

312
00:24:28,630 --> 00:24:30,840
I won't push you
if you don't want to.

313
00:24:32,920 --> 00:24:35,000
How do you know I don't want to?

314
00:25:02,840 --> 00:25:04,000
You're blushing.

315
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:07,720
No, I'm not.

316
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:09,400
Sure, you're not.

317
00:25:09,690 --> 00:25:10,840
Don't tease me.

318
00:25:11,240 --> 00:25:12,840
Did you ask my permission for that?

319
00:25:13,260 --> 00:25:15,480
You stole a kiss on my cheek.

320
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:18,680
Fair point. We're even.

321
00:25:39,540 --> 00:25:40,540
Hey.

322
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,240
That's it for today.

323
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:44,840
To be continued.

324
00:25:54,110 --> 00:25:55,110
Come on.

325
00:26:37,130 --> 00:26:38,130
Hey.

326
00:26:39,530 --> 00:26:40,930
I got the Anan card.

327
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,240
Hey.

328
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:44,400
Mine's Somporn.

329
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,480
- Wow.
- Oh, wow.

330
00:26:47,690 --> 00:26:50,080
Feels like ages
since we last picked up a book.

331
00:26:50,350 --> 00:26:53,240
True. It's been many years.

332
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:56,560
- All is well?
- Oh, yes, sir.

333
00:26:56,660 --> 00:26:59,240
Every order has been delivered.
All is well.

334
00:26:59,780 --> 00:27:03,480
Thank you for the publishing
and delivery.

335
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:06,640
Doing all that myself
would have been a mess.

336
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:08,480
- Heh.
- Happy to help, sir.

337
00:27:08,860 --> 00:27:09,600
Very well.

338
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,720
Uh, and no commission cut, right?

339
00:27:11,750 --> 00:27:13,080
Oh, none at all.

340
00:27:13,390 --> 00:27:17,040
Khun Somsak hired us to
handle the printing and delivery.

341
00:27:17,180 --> 00:27:20,280
He holds the copyright
to this novel.

342
00:27:20,310 --> 00:27:21,920
- Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

343
00:27:22,070 --> 00:27:24,650
And when does
the next print run start?

344
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:27,080
About a month from now.

345
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:29,440
Pre-orders keep coming in.

346
00:27:29,670 --> 00:27:31,680
- Hoo.
- Heh.

347
00:27:31,710 --> 00:27:32,710
So.

348
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:35,760
Grandpa, we're going to be rich.

349
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:37,310
- Heh.
- Haha.

350
00:27:37,600 --> 00:27:39,190
- Oh, my.
- Silly girl.

351
00:27:39,190 --> 00:27:40,310
- Haha.
- Haha.

352
00:27:42,970 --> 00:27:46,230
Everyone, snacks and novel are
now available in the live stream.

353
00:27:46,970 --> 00:27:48,700
E-book versions are available too.

354
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:52,720
"Are you two together now?"

355
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:54,720
How about that, everyone?

356
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,160
Does it show?

357
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:03,520
If it doesn't yet,
we'll make it more obvious.

358
00:28:06,810 --> 00:28:08,560
Save, come here.

359
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:12,520
Not now, Mom.
The views are climbing.

360
00:28:12,520 --> 00:28:16,400
Come now. Guy too.
Help me carry these.

361
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:19,190
Huh, just when
it's getting good, huh?

362
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:27,840
Great-grandma, you're in charge.

363
00:28:35,590 --> 00:28:38,230
She must keep moving.
It's the rules.

364
00:28:40,100 --> 00:28:41,100
Hey.

365
00:28:42,170 --> 00:28:45,170
Here...slowly, okay?

366
00:28:45,630 --> 00:28:46,670
Don't overdo it.

367
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:49,920
Keep an eye on her.
We'll be right back.

368
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:52,930
- Go.
- Go.

369
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:02,350
Thanks a lot, Great-grandma.

370
00:29:09,710 --> 00:29:11,440
Oh, no. This is bad.

371
00:29:11,920 --> 00:29:12,920
What?

372
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:17,520
Everyone, did she eat the sweets?

373
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:20,680
Let me cut the stream.
Be right back.

374
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:25,720
What happened?

375
00:29:25,750 --> 00:29:28,910
If she has the sweets,
Mom's gonna be in big trouble

376
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:32,720
for adapting her Royal recipe.
Now she knows.

377
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:41,960
I'm truly sorry, Grandmother.

378
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:46,280
I really need to adjust the recipe
for modern tastes.

379
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:50,160
That's right.
Otherwise it wouldn't sell.

380
00:29:50,190 --> 00:29:53,790
People nowadays can't handle
throat-burning snacks anymore.

381
00:29:54,270 --> 00:29:57,320
We added other ingredients

382
00:29:57,550 --> 00:30:01,000
just to...mellow the flavor.

383
00:30:08,650 --> 00:30:09,650
Oh.

384
00:30:19,420 --> 00:30:22,230
Hmm? Looks like she likes it.

385
00:30:22,370 --> 00:30:23,370
Hmm?

386
00:30:23,620 --> 00:30:24,940
We've kept it from her.

387
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:27,210
- But she actually likes it.
- Mm-hmm.

388
00:30:27,210 --> 00:30:31,080
I told you.
You were overthinking it.

389
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:33,240
Good things speak for themselves.

390
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,280
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

391
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:36,960
When did you tell me exactly?
I don't remember.

392
00:30:37,790 --> 00:30:40,430
I told you, why bother
hiding it from her?

393
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:44,420
Phi Sorn, you were just
as scared of her reaction.

394
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:47,280
That's why we've been hiding it.
Come on.

395
00:30:49,270 --> 00:30:50,320
Oh, hey.

396
00:30:50,790 --> 00:30:52,400
- She's having more.
- Yeah.

397
00:30:52,900 --> 00:30:53,990
Hmm...

398
00:30:55,290 --> 00:30:56,390
All right.

399
00:31:02,900 --> 00:31:04,250
- Guy.
- Yeah?

400
00:31:06,480 --> 00:31:09,480
What's wrong?
Acting strange all day.

401
00:31:10,930 --> 00:31:12,320
Am I? I'm fine.

402
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:13,680
Not fine.

403
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:17,110
If you're fine, we'd have
gotten back here for dinner.

404
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:20,560
Instead, you've had me take you
all over town.

405
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:24,200
Come on. Let's go inside.

406
00:31:31,580 --> 00:31:32,640
Hello, Phi Cha.

407
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,120
Hello.

408
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:35,520
Oh, hi Phi Cha.

409
00:31:37,030 --> 00:31:38,120
What brings you here?

410
00:31:39,780 --> 00:31:41,760
Hmm? Didn't Guy tell you?

411
00:31:43,430 --> 00:31:45,200
I wanted to surprise you.

412
00:31:48,500 --> 00:31:52,920
I'm here to tell you that
we'd like to sign both of you.

413
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:54,520
Seriously?

414
00:31:54,550 --> 00:32:00,040
Absolutely. But you mentioned
your father had some concerns.

415
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:03,040
So I'm here to
clear things up with him.

416
00:32:03,190 --> 00:32:05,700
Oh, no concerns now.

417
00:32:05,910 --> 00:32:08,690
Well, a grown man
makes his own choices.

418
00:32:09,020 --> 00:32:10,220
Really?

419
00:32:10,260 --> 00:32:13,280
Really. Just don't
let your grades slip.

420
00:32:13,630 --> 00:32:16,880
You've come a long way.

421
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:21,720
So what do they need to do next?

422
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:25,320
We'll arrange for them to come in
and sign the contract.

423
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:27,320
You are welcome to come along.

424
00:32:28,070 --> 00:32:29,070
Yeah.

425
00:32:29,210 --> 00:32:32,450
Please come,
in case I panic or something.

426
00:32:33,070 --> 00:32:36,890
Hey, you're grown.
Start handling things yourself.

427
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:37,920
Hmph.

428
00:32:38,850 --> 00:32:42,300
- Uh, sir. There's one more thing.
- Yes.

429
00:32:42,300 --> 00:32:44,920
Our studio would like to
acquire the rights to

430
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:48,240
Between Us in the Deep Forest
to adapt as a series.

431
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:52,600
Might I ask if you'd already
sold the rights to anyone?

432
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:03,000
So have you
sold the rights to anyone yet?

433
00:33:03,850 --> 00:33:07,680
Not yet.
You're actually the first to ask.

434
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:11,000
Would you consider us?

435
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:12,600
Yes,...absolutely.

436
00:33:13,080 --> 00:33:14,320
She asked your grandpa.

437
00:33:16,250 --> 00:33:20,280
Well, if you want to turn this into

438
00:33:20,730 --> 00:33:23,400
a film or a drama, no objections.

439
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:28,200
Just one condition:

440
00:33:28,230 --> 00:33:31,190
keep the heart of the novel intact.

441
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:35,200
The rest you can adapt
however it suits you.

442
00:33:37,130 --> 00:33:41,520
Thank you so much, sir.
Your novel is truly wonderful.

443
00:33:41,990 --> 00:33:45,200
We promise to honor
the source material as best we can.

444
00:33:46,380 --> 00:33:49,600
Can I have some say in casting?

445
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:53,000
Right now we're looking at

446
00:33:53,020 --> 00:33:55,150
Save and Nong Guy for the leads.

447
00:33:55,730 --> 00:33:56,730
Hey.

448
00:33:59,010 --> 00:34:01,400
Well...no objections.

449
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,960
Grandpa, time to wake up.

450
00:34:20,420 --> 00:34:21,420
Grandpa.

451
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:23,440
Grandpa.

452
00:34:28,740 --> 00:34:29,740
Grandpa.

453
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,320
Grandpa.

454
00:34:32,560 --> 00:34:33,560
Grandpa.

455
00:34:33,790 --> 00:34:34,790
Grandpa.

456
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:37,760
Oh...Grandpa.

457
00:34:41,160 --> 00:34:42,910
Today, you're going under the knife.

458
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:44,600
I'm a person, not a piece of pork.

459
00:34:45,600 --> 00:34:48,520
Come on. Up, up.

460
00:34:48,820 --> 00:34:50,720
Ugh, what were you thinking?

461
00:34:50,930 --> 00:34:54,020
Are they doing both eyes today?

462
00:34:54,460 --> 00:34:57,060
See? You weren't
listening to the doctor.

463
00:34:57,270 --> 00:34:59,840
One at a time, two weeks apart.

464
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:01,640
Oh, now I remember.

465
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:05,280
Walk slowly.

466
00:35:05,550 --> 00:35:06,550
Watch your step.

467
00:35:08,780 --> 00:35:10,200
Ready, Father?

468
00:35:10,600 --> 00:35:13,080
I've been ready.
Can't wait to see clearly.

469
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,480
Yeah.

470
00:35:14,510 --> 00:35:16,970
Nothing to worry about.
You'll be perfectly safe.

471
00:35:17,420 --> 00:35:18,440
Thank you.

472
00:35:18,440 --> 00:35:19,280
Heh.

473
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:20,320
Shall we go then?

474
00:35:20,320 --> 00:35:21,680
- Mm-hmm.
- What about Sun?

475
00:35:22,370 --> 00:35:24,360
He'll meet us at the hospital.

476
00:35:24,940 --> 00:35:25,940
Oh, okay.

477
00:35:25,970 --> 00:35:26,970
Wait, wait.

478
00:35:35,430 --> 00:35:36,430
Yeah.

479
00:35:37,010 --> 00:35:38,020
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

480
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:45,360
The left eye surgery went smoothly.

481
00:35:45,760 --> 00:35:49,680
So I'll have normal vision again?

482
00:35:49,940 --> 00:35:54,280
Yes, the cornea may still be
a little swollen at first.

483
00:35:54,450 --> 00:35:58,880
Your vision will improve gradually,
but not quite a hundred percent yet.

484
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:02,320
You can go home now.

485
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:06,440
See you in two weeks
for the right eye.

486
00:36:06,550 --> 00:36:07,990
Thank you very much.

487
00:36:08,020 --> 00:36:09,020
Okay.

488
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:10,160
- Thank you.
- Thank you.
Thank you.

489
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:31,140
"Two weeks later"

490
00:36:38,150 --> 00:36:39,520
We're home, Dad.

491
00:36:40,230 --> 00:36:41,500
Easy now, easy.

492
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:42,440
Careful, careful.

493
00:36:42,460 --> 00:36:44,020
- Gently, Dad.
- Easy. Right here.

494
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:45,240
- Oh?
- Easy, easy.

495
00:36:45,260 --> 00:36:46,670
Alright, alright.

496
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:49,920
I can see. I can walk on my own.

497
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:52,200
It's not the vision
I'm worried about.

498
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:53,560
It's the age.

499
00:36:53,560 --> 00:36:55,920
Didn't you take a tumble
in front of the nurses?

500
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:56,680
He did.

501
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:59,600
My, my.

502
00:36:59,630 --> 00:37:02,640
You two are finishing
each other's sentences now.

503
00:37:02,660 --> 00:37:04,000
Haha.

504
00:37:05,050 --> 00:37:06,120
Take it slow, Dad.

505
00:37:06,310 --> 00:37:09,710
- Grandpa.
- Grandpa.

506
00:37:09,870 --> 00:37:11,280
Gently, gently.

507
00:37:11,280 --> 00:37:12,400
How are you feeling?

508
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:14,400
Good and fine.

509
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:17,520
Ahem.

510
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:24,200
"Check: 200,000 baht"
Here you go.

511
00:37:25,330 --> 00:37:28,160
Saeng Karun alumni from nearly
every generation sent this.

512
00:37:29,560 --> 00:37:31,360
Did you go around
collecting from them?

513
00:37:31,590 --> 00:37:35,850
No, they caught the news
about your novel and did this.

514
00:37:36,440 --> 00:37:37,920
I won't accept it. Give it back.

515
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:43,040
Nope, can't give it back.
They said to keep it.

516
00:37:43,040 --> 00:37:46,000
They want to support the home
that raised them too.

517
00:37:48,350 --> 00:37:51,880
- Just accept it, Father.
- Mm-hmm.

518
00:37:52,940 --> 00:37:53,940
Here.

519
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:01,600
Could you sign this for me, sir?

520
00:38:02,070 --> 00:38:03,800
Oh, of course.

521
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:07,960
Doing my grandfather a favor.

522
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,280
- Sure.
- Hand it over.

523
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:22,160
He said you inspired
his entire generation.

524
00:38:23,280 --> 00:38:24,480
Me?

525
00:38:24,480 --> 00:38:28,520
Yeah, his grandpa used to just
sit around at home.

526
00:38:28,850 --> 00:38:31,040
Now he gets up
and paints every day.

527
00:38:31,810 --> 00:38:33,380
He always dreamed of
being an artist.

528
00:38:33,530 --> 00:38:36,320
Oh...good for him.

529
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:41,640
Well then,
may he find great success.

530
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:44,780
- Thank you so much.
- Yeah.

531
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:49,880
Come on. The first episode
of the series is coming on.

532
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:53,440
Hmph.

533
00:39:03,450 --> 00:39:06,720
It's our debut. Don't go too hard
on the comments, okay?

534
00:39:07,040 --> 00:39:08,960
Okay, I'll tone it down.

535
00:39:08,990 --> 00:39:10,320
Aw...I'm feeling it already.

536
00:39:13,290 --> 00:39:16,440
"We go in and the only way out
is through."

537
00:39:16,440 --> 00:39:18,120
"Do I look terrified?"

538
00:39:18,520 --> 00:39:19,920
"Just making sure one last time."

539
00:39:21,310 --> 00:39:24,240
"I reckoned danger awaited.
Yet here I stand with you."

540
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:28,280
"Then...swear you won't die."

541
00:39:29,090 --> 00:39:31,560
"Only fools swear
to something like that."

542
00:39:33,180 --> 00:39:35,080
"Fool or not, just swear..."

543
00:39:35,600 --> 00:39:37,440
"that you'll walk away from this."

544
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:42,560
"I'll walk away with you,
even through hellfire."

545
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:44,480
"That I swear."

546
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:56,240
- Wow.
- Sweet.

547
00:39:56,690 --> 00:39:57,920
What's wrong? Heh.

548
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:00,040
It's so sweet, Phi Save.

549
00:40:00,630 --> 00:40:02,960
They just hold hands.

550
00:40:09,660 --> 00:40:10,660
"Oh, ugh."

551
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:15,280
"Tch."

552
00:40:46,380 --> 00:40:47,720
Deeply in it, huh?

553
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:52,160
Thank you.

554
00:41:00,090 --> 00:41:03,160
From all of us, together.

555
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:06,800
Selling sweets, selling novels.

556
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:09,120
In Thai and English too.

557
00:41:09,440 --> 00:41:10,720
Audiobooks.

558
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:13,760
Selling the novel rights
for the series adaptation.

559
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:17,600
And...Save's acting fee.

560
00:41:19,020 --> 00:41:20,150
Haha.

561
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:23,880
The remaining bank debt is down to

562
00:41:24,070 --> 00:41:27,160
just two million baht.

563
00:41:27,190 --> 00:41:30,840
- Yay.
- Yes...

564
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:33,020
Hmph...unbelievable.

565
00:41:33,460 --> 00:41:35,340
Everyone's done an incredible job.

566
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:38,680
You helped manage
the household accounts,

567
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:40,760
so we could plan a large repayment.

568
00:41:40,780 --> 00:41:41,800
Happy to help.

569
00:41:42,030 --> 00:41:44,880
- This calls for a celebration.
- Yay.

570
00:41:45,360 --> 00:41:48,100
Then we'll celebrate you
getting your sight back too.

571
00:41:48,720 --> 00:41:51,440
I have to thank everyone once more

572
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:56,980
that Saeng Karun is
still standing today.

573
00:42:00,370 --> 00:42:04,760
Now I could face my grandfather,
unashamed.

574
00:42:19,940 --> 00:42:23,880
Oh, by the way,
our reader-fan next door

575
00:42:23,880 --> 00:42:25,720
has a bunch of oranges for us.

576
00:42:26,660 --> 00:42:29,260
Guy, take some home for your family.

577
00:42:30,050 --> 00:42:31,620
- Yes, Dad.
- Mm-hmm.

578
00:42:31,860 --> 00:42:33,490
I'll help you carry them.

579
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:35,440
Sure. Let's go now.

580
00:42:39,700 --> 00:42:42,360
Looks like your dad
is warming up to Guy.

581
00:42:48,020 --> 00:42:49,360
Will you finish all of those?

582
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:52,600
I can pass them on to the neighbors.

583
00:42:52,780 --> 00:42:54,000
Feeling better?

584
00:42:55,400 --> 00:42:57,000
My dad's coming around to you now.

585
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:59,920
Honestly, he's been nice to me
for a while.

586
00:43:00,260 --> 00:43:01,490
Well, you're easy to like.

587
00:43:02,240 --> 00:43:04,080
I told you he'd soften up.

588
00:43:04,780 --> 00:43:07,440
You think...we'll change?

589
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:10,320
You mean when we get more famous?

590
00:43:11,600 --> 00:43:12,600
Mm-hmm.

591
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:16,800
Maybe...a little more
full of ourselves.

592
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:18,560
Seriously.

593
00:43:19,200 --> 00:43:20,200
Oh.

594
00:43:21,310 --> 00:43:22,390
Hmm...

595
00:43:23,920 --> 00:43:25,320
Who knows what the future holds?

596
00:43:25,570 --> 00:43:27,530
Our series might be a total dud.

597
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:30,360
Or you might
get tired of me first.

598
00:43:30,880 --> 00:43:33,800
But right now, I love

599
00:43:35,360 --> 00:43:36,920
having you by my side.

600
00:43:38,580 --> 00:43:40,360
Figuring it out together.

601
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:43,120
Same.

602
00:43:45,080 --> 00:43:47,080
There's still so much
I want to do with you.

603
00:43:56,240 --> 00:43:57,680
So don't get tired of me yet.

604
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:17,960
"Bank deposit: 47,500 baht"

605
00:44:18,050 --> 00:44:19,050
Hmm?

606
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:21,120
I got a bank deposit?

607
00:44:22,240 --> 00:44:24,640
I...sent you that money.

608
00:44:25,960 --> 00:44:28,480
What for? And why?

609
00:44:29,470 --> 00:44:32,030
Well, since I graduated,

610
00:44:32,550 --> 00:44:35,000
I've never really
given you anything.

611
00:44:36,560 --> 00:44:38,410
Whenever I tried, you'd say,

612
00:44:38,470 --> 00:44:41,720
"Only if you stand
on your own first. I'm fine."

613
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:45,280
I've saved up...for three years

614
00:44:45,930 --> 00:44:47,810
from food delivery runs.

615
00:44:48,400 --> 00:44:50,240
After family responsibilities, I had

616
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:51,960
about this much.

617
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:54,720
It's not a lot.

618
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:58,120
But I wanted to give it to you.

619
00:45:01,300 --> 00:45:02,300
You did good.

620
00:45:07,350 --> 00:45:09,520
I always knew...
you had it in you.

621
00:45:10,870 --> 00:45:11,870
Heh.

622
00:45:15,840 --> 00:45:18,080
Me? I've always had it, Dad.

623
00:45:18,080 --> 00:45:20,640
- Just keeping it low-key.
- Yeah.

624
00:45:23,320 --> 00:45:25,840
Alright, I'mma help Mart
with the sweets.

625
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:27,160
Yeah.

626
00:46:01,030 --> 00:46:02,070
Not turning in yet?

627
00:46:02,090 --> 00:46:04,840
Not yet. Taking a break, really.

628
00:46:07,710 --> 00:46:08,710
Okay.

629
00:46:10,230 --> 00:46:12,060
- Has Uncle Sun filled you in?
- Hmm?

630
00:46:12,080 --> 00:46:14,640
People are loving the first episode,

631
00:46:14,960 --> 00:46:17,250
and raving about the source novel.

632
00:46:17,600 --> 00:46:19,080
Sales are going to shoot up.

633
00:46:21,040 --> 00:46:25,410
I have to thank you too,
for making all of this happen.

634
00:46:26,600 --> 00:46:29,240
You should be thanking yourself
most of all.

635
00:46:30,370 --> 00:46:32,520
Hope your series really takes off.

636
00:46:33,200 --> 00:46:34,880
Sathu...

637
00:46:35,490 --> 00:46:38,760
Keep it coming
so I can take care of you.

638
00:46:39,010 --> 00:46:42,680
Oh, I'm fine.
I can take care of myself.

639
00:46:42,960 --> 00:46:44,800
There's still so much I can do.

640
00:46:45,200 --> 00:46:47,060
Clear eyes, sharp mind, huh?

641
00:46:47,220 --> 00:46:51,240
See what I'll cook up
when my eyes are fully healed.

642
00:46:52,320 --> 00:46:53,320
Cook up what?

643
00:46:53,660 --> 00:46:55,080
Brand new thing.

644
00:46:55,230 --> 00:46:56,230
Huh?

645
00:46:58,880 --> 00:47:03,440
"Guys, gals. Between Us
in the Deep Forest is insane."

646
00:47:03,440 --> 00:47:05,640
"And I heard through the grapevine"

647
00:47:05,640 --> 00:47:08,280
"that Save and Guy
are actually together."

648
00:47:08,280 --> 00:47:09,760
"But keep it quiet."

649
00:47:09,800 --> 00:47:13,160
"They'd rather sell their work
than that angle."

650
00:47:13,160 --> 00:47:15,160
"You and your nephew are huge now."

651
00:47:15,310 --> 00:47:17,560
"Congrats on Save's series too."

652
00:47:17,590 --> 00:47:22,280
"Thanks.
I am very proud of him too."

653
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:26,200
"Can you share your key to success?"

654
00:47:26,680 --> 00:47:28,240
"Key to success?"

655
00:47:29,660 --> 00:47:35,240
"It depends on
how you define success."

656
00:47:36,320 --> 00:47:39,400
"As for me, I'm not sure I've ever"

657
00:47:39,400 --> 00:47:42,000
"held the key to my own success."

658
00:47:43,080 --> 00:47:46,040
"But...if I must answer..."

659
00:47:50,850 --> 00:47:56,800
First, my family,
for their unwavering support.

660
00:47:58,080 --> 00:48:02,240
Second, keeping an open mind.

661
00:48:03,040 --> 00:48:06,560
When I had to write a BL novel,

662
00:48:08,010 --> 00:48:10,760
I started talking more
with my grandchildren.

663
00:48:11,680 --> 00:48:14,000
I learned more
about the modern world

664
00:48:14,830 --> 00:48:18,470
and exchanged ideas
with a younger generation.

665
00:48:19,030 --> 00:48:22,560
It broadened my perspective.

666
00:48:23,480 --> 00:48:26,480
I think the reason more people
are reading my novel now

667
00:48:27,070 --> 00:48:32,280
is because
I was willing to change.

668
00:48:32,920 --> 00:48:36,360
"Anything you would like
to say to young people"

669
00:48:36,360 --> 00:48:38,760
"who want to find success?"

670
00:48:39,310 --> 00:48:42,840
"Young people today
put so much pressure on themselves."

671
00:48:43,440 --> 00:48:47,320
Really, they should grow
gradually at their own pace.

672
00:48:49,020 --> 00:48:50,440
Life isn't a race.

673
00:48:51,030 --> 00:48:52,400
There's no need to rush.

674
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:55,440
If they fall, rise and walk again.

675
00:48:56,360 --> 00:48:58,400
Too hard to go on?
Then sit and rest.

676
00:48:59,560 --> 00:49:02,760
Make every moment count.

677
00:49:03,230 --> 00:49:07,680
Change will come. Learn to adapt.

678
00:49:08,400 --> 00:49:11,230
But more than anything...

679
00:49:11,670 --> 00:49:15,680
no matter fortune
life brings one day,

680
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:17,560
be it fame,

681
00:49:18,360 --> 00:49:21,520
money, or worldly gain,

682
00:49:33,320 --> 00:49:34,910
remember that none of it lasts.

683
00:49:36,990 --> 00:49:39,880
Happiness is fleeting.

684
00:49:44,450 --> 00:49:45,600
And suffering, too,

685
00:49:47,150 --> 00:49:48,920
shall pass.

686
00:49:51,120 --> 00:49:54,840
One day, we all leave this world.

687
00:49:56,440 --> 00:49:58,090
Part of who we were

688
00:49:58,520 --> 00:50:01,640
may linger in the memories
of those still here,

689
00:50:04,440 --> 00:50:07,400
and may eventually be forgotten.

690
00:50:08,440 --> 00:50:13,480
Eventually, all things turn

691
00:50:13,890 --> 00:50:15,840
in the great wheel of life.

692
00:50:16,160 --> 00:50:17,130
Everyone...
Look at this.

693
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:19,260
- Everyone.
- Everyone.

694
00:50:19,840 --> 00:50:20,600
- Oh-ho.
- Wow.
Look...

695
00:50:21,150 --> 00:50:22,150
Come, come.

696
00:50:22,790 --> 00:50:24,850
- Oh-ho.
- Wow.

697
00:50:24,950 --> 00:50:26,920
At last, vegetables to eat.

698
00:50:27,120 --> 00:50:29,680
- Yay.
- Yes.

699
00:51:10,780 --> 00:51:11,960
- Grandpa.
- Hmm?

700
00:51:12,790 --> 00:51:14,000
What's the bell for?

701
00:51:15,680 --> 00:51:16,880
To wake up the kids.

702
00:51:17,380 --> 00:51:19,240
What about...your bugle?

703
00:51:19,580 --> 00:51:20,840
Can't manage it anymore.

704
00:51:22,360 --> 00:51:23,640
Where did you get it?

705
00:51:24,240 --> 00:51:27,280
It was Grandpa's.
He used it back in the old days.

706
00:51:27,610 --> 00:51:29,770
If it still works, use it.

707
00:51:30,520 --> 00:51:32,240
- Come on. Give me that.
- Ha?

708
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:34,400
I'll help. Come here.

709
00:51:37,100 --> 00:51:38,620
Easy, easy.

710
00:51:38,950 --> 00:51:40,120
Hang it here?

711
00:51:49,380 --> 00:51:50,640
There...

712
00:51:58,200 --> 00:52:00,090
Six o'clock. Right on the dot.

713
00:52:00,480 --> 00:52:01,480
Exactly.

714
00:52:25,600 --> 00:52:26,930
Rise and shine, everyone.

715
00:52:35,500 --> 00:52:38,120
The clock keeps ticking,
never still.

716
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:40,920
As time rolls on
beyond our will.

717
00:52:40,920 --> 00:52:45,760
The seasons turn
in endless style.

718
00:52:46,680 --> 00:52:49,000
We break down and cry.

719
00:52:49,520 --> 00:52:51,520
Sometimes we smile.

720
00:52:51,520 --> 00:52:55,480
Nothing stands still,
even if we try.

721
00:52:56,120 --> 00:52:59,880
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

722
00:52:59,880 --> 00:53:03,480
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

723
00:53:03,480 --> 00:53:08,640
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

724
00:53:08,640 --> 00:53:11,040
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

725
00:53:11,040 --> 00:53:13,880
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

726
00:53:13,880 --> 00:53:18,440
And land where
our hearts both grow.

727
00:53:24,060 --> 00:53:29,920
The world keeps
turning every day.

728
00:53:29,920 --> 00:53:35,280
And we keep
turning in its play.

729
00:53:35,280 --> 00:53:38,680
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

730
00:53:38,680 --> 00:53:41,120
We just might see
the world within.

731
00:53:41,120 --> 00:53:45,280
Let's walk together,
day by day.

732
00:53:45,280 --> 00:53:51,640
Come take the step,
what do you say?

